<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <meta name="description" content="REST API reference for bStats.">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/>
    <title>bStats — REST API</title>

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/stylesheets/tailwind.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"/>
    <link href="/stylesheets/style.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"/>
</head>
<body class="bg-slate-950 text-slate-100 antialiased">

<% include ../templates/navigation.ejs %>

<main>
    <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-950 via-slate-900 to-slate-950"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-[-18rem] -z-20 flex justify-center opacity-70 blur-3xl">
            <div class="h-[26rem] w-[60rem] max-w-full" style="background: radial-gradient(circle at top, var(--accent-color) 0%, rgba(15,118,110,0) 65%);"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-24 sm:py-28 lg:py-32">
            <div class="space-y-6 text-center">
                <span class="accent-pill inline-flex text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em]">Documentation</span>
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-5xl">REST API</h1>
                <p class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-7 text-slate-300">Fetch plugin metadata and chart data programmatically. The API is read-only and uses simple JSON responses.</p>
            </div>

            <aside class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6 text-left text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
                <p class="font-semibold text-white">Base URL</p>
                <p class="mt-2"><code class="rounded bg-slate-900/60 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-white">https://bstats.org/api/v1</code></p>
                <p class="mt-4">All endpoints accept <span class="font-semibold text-white">GET</span> requests only. Use <code class="rounded bg-slate-900/60 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs">Accept: application/json</code> to ensure JSON responses.</p>
            </aside>

            <div class="mt-16 space-y-10">
                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">List plugins</h2>
                        <code class="rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/70">GET /plugins</code>
                    </header>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Return all tracked plugins including ID, name, owner and platform. Useful for directories or search indexes.</p>
                    <pre class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-xs leading-6 text-slate-200"><code>[
  {
    "id": 1337,
    "name": "ExamplePlugin",
    "owner": { "id": 42, "name": "ExampleUser" },
    "software": { "id": 1, "name": "Bukkit / Spigot", "url": "bukkit" },
    "isGlobal": false
  }
]</code></pre>
                </article>

                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Plugin details</h2>
                        <code class="rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/70">GET /plugins/{pluginId}</code>
                    </header>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Returns metadata for a specific plugin, plus its chart definitions.</p>
                    <pre class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-xs leading-6 text-slate-200"><code>{
  "id": 1337,
  "name": "ExamplePlugin",
  "owner": { "id": 42, "name": "ExampleUser" },
  "charts": {
    "players": {
      "uid": 1234,
      "type": "single_linechart",
      "position": 0,
      "title": "Players",
      "isDefault": true,
      "data": {
        "lineName": "Players",
        "filter": { "enabled": false, "maxValue": 1, "minValue": 1 }
      }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
                </article>

                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">List charts</h2>
                        <code class="rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/70">GET /plugins/{pluginId}/charts</code>
                    </header>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Fetch every chart belonging to a plugin. Combine with the data endpoint for values.</p>
                    <pre class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-xs leading-6 text-slate-200"><code>{
  "players": {
    "uid": 1234,
    "type": "single_linechart",
    "position": 0,
    "title": "Players",
    "isDefault": true,
    "data": {
      "lineName": "Players",
      "filter": { "enabled": false, "maxValue": 1, "minValue": 1 }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
                </article>

                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Chart metadata</h2>
                        <code class="rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/70">GET /plugins/{pluginId}/charts/{chartId}</code>
                    </header>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Inspect a single chart by its ID.</p>
                    <pre class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-xs leading-6 text-slate-200"><code>{
  "uid": 1234,
  "type": "single_linechart",
  "position": 0,
  "title": "Players",
  "isDefault": true,
  "data": {
    "lineName": "Players",
    "filter": { "enabled": false, "maxValue": 1, "minValue": 1 }
  }
}</code></pre>
                </article>

                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Chart data</h2>
                        <code class="rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/70">GET /plugins/{pluginId}/charts/{chartId}/data</code>
                    </header>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Returns data points for the specified chart. The format depends on chart type. For line charts, it’s <code class="rounded bg-slate-900/60 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs">[timestamp, value]</code>.</p>
                    <pre class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-xs leading-6 text-slate-200"><code>[
  [1479799800000, 122],
  [1479801600000, 121],
  [1479803400000, 124],
  [1479805200000, 134]
]</code></pre>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Use <code class="rounded bg-slate-900/60 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs">?maxElements={amount}</code> to limit results (default ≈ one month for line charts).</p>
                </article>

                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Server software</h2>
                        <code class="rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/70">GET /software</code>
                    </header>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">List all supported platforms and the associated global statistics plugin.</p>
                    <pre class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-xs leading-6 text-slate-200"><code>[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Bukkit / Spigot",
    "url": "bukkit",
    "globalPlugin": { "id": 1, "name": "_bukkit_" }
  }
]</code></pre>
                </article>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-16 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
                <p class="font-semibold text-white">Rate limits & caching</p>
                <p class="mt-2">Responses are cached briefly (≈ 30 seconds). Please avoid aggressive polling; we recommend refreshing charts every few minutes at most.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

<% include ../templates/footer.ejs %>
<% include ../templates/globalScripts.ejs %>

</body>
</html>
